cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.DC, cs.GT. 

The problem involves manipulating intervals on a line, which is a classic computational geometry problem, hence cs.CG is the most likely sub-category. The algorithmic technique used in the paper involves observations and pruning, which are common techniques in data structures and algorithms, hence cs.DS is also likely. The problem also involves ordering intervals, which is a combinatorial problem, hence cs.DM and cs.DC are also likely. Finally, the problem involves optimizing a certain objective function, which is a common theme in game theory, hence cs.GT is also a possible sub-category.
